title: ADOPTABLE PET: Living Free
text:
Published: Oct. 21, 2015 9:59 a.m. ADOPTABLE PET: Living Free Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Calypso, a shepherd/hound mix, is available for adoption. COURTESY OF LIVING FREE Related article » Animal’s name: Calypso
Breed: Male shepherd/hound mix
Date of birth: Aug. 5, 2009
Weight: 40 pounds
About the animal: Calypso is a friendly, curious dog that enjoys the company of humans. He loves his daily walks and playing with his kennel mates at the park. He is house-trained with a doggie door.
Agency: Living Free, a donor supported, nonprofit, no kill animal sanctuary
Location: 54250 Keen Camp Road in Mountain Center off Highway 74, 15 minutes from Idyllwild
Information: 951-321-9982 or to view all of Living Free’s adoptable dogs and cats, go to living-free.org .
Contact the writer: community@pe.com
